{{oneref|date=December 2010}} '''Metadata Authority Description Schema''' (MADS) is an [[XML schema]] developed by the United States [[Library of Congress]]' Network Development and Standards Office that provides an [[authority control|authority]] element set to complement the [[Metadata Object Description Schema]] (MODS).<ref>{{cite journal | title = Standards Update: Some Interesting XML Standards | author = Mark Needleman | journal = [[Serials Review]] | volume = 31 | issue = 1 | date = March 2005 | pages = 70–71 | doi = 10.1016/j.serrev.2004.11.012 }}</ref>
